    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>Key Differences Between Keto and Standard Macros</h2>
      <p>
        The ketogenic diet and standard balanced macronutrient approaches represent two fundamentally different philosophies about how to fuel your body. The keto diet drastically restricts carbohydrates to force the body into ketosis — a metabolic state where fat becomes the primary fuel source. Standard macro diets maintain a balanced split of all three macronutrients, relying on carbohydrates as the body's preferred energy source. Both approaches can be effective for different goals, but they differ significantly in food choices, sustainability, and physiological effects.
      </p>

